We will make a 8555 ACME endpoint that uses out issuing SSL CA, requirements are:
    * serves a directory will all required paths
    * Do domain validation using either http-01 or dns-01 (we have this in cert_factory.php)
    * uses our https://thameur.org/ct/v1/ to get the required number of CT as per the validity period
    supports both ECC and RSA and uses the ECC or the RSA, no algorithm mixing in the same tree (cert_factory.php does this)
    * make a doc page acmews.php and create its card in "Certificate Issuance & Test CAs" to replace the blurred once
    * Certbot and 8555 clients will be able to create account, get an EULA to accept, renew (treat it as a new issuance), and revoke certificates anytime
    * 90 days validity
    * No EAB
    * The CSR created by the tool will carry the domains (parent, subdomain and wildcard, so the validation need to follow the BR for each type)
    * Rate limit to avoid abuse
    * the endpoint will follow a standard ACME path under thameur.org